article.headline: Portland St. 72, Montana 45
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Sophomore forward Phil Nelson had 16 points to lead Portland State to an easy 72-45 win over Montana to open their Big Sky Conference season Saturday night. Junior forward Julius Thomas added 14 points with a career-high tying 10 rebounds for Portland State (8-3) as the Vikings claimed their 14th straight victory against Big Sky opponents at home. Portland State forced 16 Montana turnovers in the first half as they built a 36-23 lead. Then a 25-6 run midway through the second half pushed the lead to as many as 29 points. The Vikings had 23 turnovers of their own, but shot a solid .510 from the field, .500 from three-point range. Montana was only .348 from the field, as the Grizzlies fell to 6-6 for the season. Anthony Johnson led Montana with 15 points.
